Data Direction Register		$0000Peripheral Data Register	$0001	-DDR maps PDR bits to inputs or outputs	-DDR bit value of 1, means PDR bit value is outputted to I/O device	-DDR bit value of 0, means PDR bit value is inputted from I/O deviceDDR and PDR		---------------------------------register bit		| 7 | 6 | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 |default values		---------------------------------DDR = xx101111		0 - LORAMPDR = xx110111		1 - HIRAM			2 - CHAREN			3 - Cassette write data			4 - Cassette sense (0 = PLAY button depressed)			5 - Cassette motor control (0 = motor spins)			6 - unused (not available on the 6510)			7 - unused (not available on the 6510)			  -------------------------------			  *** M E M O R Y   M O D E S ***			  -------------------------------			    (LORAM, HIRAM, GAME, EXROM)	*) Only modes enterable from the default mode without any attached	   hardware are depicted.			          | DEFAULT       | 1111	 101x	 001x		Legend:-------|-------|-------|-------|	-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------  $0000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	Kernal | $E000 - $FFFF	| Kernal ROM.-------|-------|-------|-------|	-------|----------------|------------------------------------------------------ $1000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	IO/C   | $D000 - $DFFF	| I/O address space or Character-------|-------|-------|-------|	       |		| generator ROM, selected by -CHAREN. $2000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	       |		| If the CHAREN bit is clear,-------|-------|-------|-------|	       |		| the character generator ROM is $3000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	       |		| chosen. If it is set, the-------|-------|-------|-------|	       |		| I/O chips are accessible. $4000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	-------|----------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|-------|-------|-------|	BASIC  | $A000 - $BFFF	| BASIC ROM. $5000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	-------|----------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|-------|-------|-------|	RAM    | various ranges	| Commodore 64's internal RAM. $6000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |	-------|----------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|-------|-------|-------| $7000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $8000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $9000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $A000 | BASIC | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $B000 | BASIC | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $C000 | RAM   | RAM   | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $D000 | IO/C  | IO/C  | RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $E000 | KERNAL| KERNAL| RAM   |-------|-------|-------|-------| $F000 | KERNAL| KERNAL| RAM   |     